      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/36/65",
      "text": [
        " \"كُلْ إِذَا كَانَ فِي أَسْوَاقِ اَلْمُسْلِمِينَ وَ لاَ تَسْأَلْ عَنْهُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4185 - And it is narrated from Al-Fudayl, Zurara, and Muhammad ibn Muslim, from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as):\nThey asked him about buying meat from the markets without knowing what the butchers do.\nImam (as) said: \"Eat if it is in the markets of the Muslims, and do not ask about it.\""
        ]
      }
